      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TITIWHA (9) is in a purple patch of form. Made it two wins on the trot when he showed plenty of fight to salute last start at this venue, getting home by 1.2 metres. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and the sprint lane is in play. Big chance again. KUALIGHT (10) has been going well this time in and again performed admirably last time out, drawing very wide and drifting back but making up plenty of ground to place at this circuit and distance. Draws on the second line but has won from there before. May prove tough to beat. WICKED WIZARD (6) has been racing consistently in Victoria and scored an easy win over this distance the last time he raced here. Could do it again. KALKADOON DREAMING (7) draws wide but made it back-to-back placings with a respectable third at his most recent appearance here.",
